        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 6:17PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 617 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Christopher, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Vernon, Benton, Du Quoin, Christopher, Rend Lake Area, Sesser,
Valier, West City, Ina, North City, Buckner, Waltonville, Bonnie,
Ewing, Nason, and St. Johns.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 57 in Illinois between Mile Markers 70 and 96.
Interstate 64 in Illinois between Mile Markers 74 and 84.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
